title: For Sale:  Egyptian Maadi AK47 RML
postcontent:
This is not ypur typical ak. if you want a cheap in accurate bullet hose by all means help yourself to a century arms romanian or other varient i have owned plenty of those myself. But if you want a premium ak 47 read on......In almost every regard this is an exact duplicate of the Russian AKM. During the 1950's the Soviet Union, as part of its millitary aid program, established the production of Soviet-pattern small arms in the Arab Republic of Egypt. AKM rifles were manufactured at the "factory  54" the Maadi Company for Engineering Industries in Cairo. The plant was supervised  by Russians prior to their abrurpt expulsion from Egypt at the hands of Anwar Sadat in 1972. A semi automatic only version was introduced to the American public by the  U.S. division of Styer-Daimler-Punch in Styer Austria (this rifle comes standard with a styer barrel). For all intents and purposes this is as close to most of us will ever come to a Russian AKM. 
   The laminated wooden hand gaurds and buttstock are correct in every detal. The lower handgaurd has the propper swells, and the buttstock has been reinforced with the steel pins in the correct places. All the wood was imported from Finland but finished and fit in Egypt. The plastic.pistol grip was injection molded in the same molds used by the AKM. 
   The metal components are EXACTLY those of the Russian AKM. Small recesses on each side of the reciever directly over the magwell serve as mag guides.and instantly distinguish this as an AKM. 
    Rear sights are graduated to 1000 meters (with 300 meter battle sights marked "p") instead of the ak47's 800 meter maximum. Chambers and bareel are hard chromed. 
     No doubt about it,  except for the selectfire option and the markings on the reciever this IS a Soviet AKM! 
      No more than 2000 were brought in before the importation ceased making these a very rare rifle. You will not find a cleaner one. i have searched for the last 14 months. I appollogize for the long winded history lesson but ive had so many rediculous offers because people wont do their own research so i thought i would provide what i could find about it. thank you and god bless America. have a nice day.

title: For Sale:  Daewoo DH-40
postcontent:
I'm selling my Daewoo DH-40, a DA/SA .40 S&W service pistol.  Imported by Kimber when they were in Clackamas, OR, this is one seriously reliable piece of gear.

Daewoo is a proven name that makes some outstanding firearms, and this pistol is no different.  Favored by Korean Police, it is the .40 version of the ROK Military's DP-51 9mm sidearm.  I bought this gun because I was very impressed with the DP-51's performance, and was looking for a .40.

It is based on the Smith and Wesson Model 59 Semi-autos, with one slight modification.  Daewoo incorporated what they called "Triple Action", which is a way of preserving the single action trigger weight in a double action pull.  To achieve this, after the pistol is cocked, with the weapon on safe and the finger off the trigger, simply move the hammer to the home position.  When you go to fire, simply pull the trigger.  The first half of the trigger travel feels virtually meaningless but returns the hammer to the cocked position, allowing for that crisp and clean single action pull to fire the weapon.  It's hard to explain, but I've never handled a DA/SA pistol that could put a round on target faster than this gun, and I've handled a few.

It has a 4.17" Barrel, comes with the original 11 round magazine as well as 2 10 round magazines (bought during the ban).  It has some cosmetic wear, but is as functional as it was the day I brought it home.  I've put just north of 1000 rounds through it in my almost 2 decades of owning it with zero failures, and it served as my home defense gun for the entirety of that time.  I trust it completely.

Unfortunately, they are no longer imported, though Lionheart Industries has started rebranding the 9mm DP-51 (and selling them for $5-800) and they are doing well.  Holsters for the new Lionheart Pistols should work for this one as well, if you are interested.

I will miss this gun when it's gone, but I have to make room for my next gun, and it's time to make another believer out of someone out there.

I will only sell to local Missouri residents with a driver's license or preferably, a CCW permit, and will require a bill of sale. Outside of Missouri, I will require payment upfront including $20 for shipping, and the contact information of your licensed FFL
